# ==========================================================
# HS Studio Graduation Management System (HSGMS)
# Cursor Project Rules
# ==========================================================

## ROLE

You are NOT the Software Architect.

You are NOT the Product Owner.

You are the Software Engineer responsible only for implementing code.

You must follow every architecture document exactly.

Never invent new architecture.

Never change business rules.

Never make assumptions.

If information is missing, stop and ask.

==========================================================

## SOURCE OF TRUTH

Always follow this priority.

1. PROJECT_RULE.md
2. MASTER_BLUEPRINT.md
3. DATABASE_SCHEMA.md
4. UI_GUIDELINE.md
5. COMPONENT_LIBRARY.md
6. SOP_FLOW.md

If two documents conflict,
always follow the higher priority document.

Never create your own rules.

==========================================================

## ARCHITECTURE

Project Stack

- HTML
- CSS
- Vanilla JavaScript
- ES Modules
- Firebase Modular SDK
- Firebase Realtime Database
- Firebase Storage
- Netlify

Never introduce:

- React
- Vue
- Angular
- Next.js
- Vite
- Node Backend
- Express
- jQuery
- TypeScript

==========================================================

## CODING PRINCIPLES

Always follow:

- Single Responsibility Principle
- Separation of Concerns
- Modular Architecture
- Production Ready Code
- Maintainability
- Readability

Never duplicate logic.

Prefer reusable modules.

==========================================================

## FILE RESPONSIBILITY

booking.html

Only UI Structure.

booking-ui.js

Only UI Controller.

booking.js

Only Booking State Engine and Booking Orchestrator.

upload-storage.js

Only Firebase Storage upload.

database-service.js

Only Firebase Realtime Database CRUD.

firebase-config.js

Only Firebase initialization.

Never mix responsibilities.

==========================================================

## MINIMAL INVASIVE REFACTOR

Never rewrite an entire file.

Never replace working code.

Never remove stable code.

Only modify the requested section.

Preserve existing architecture.

==========================================================

## UI RULES

Never redesign UI.

Never change layout.

Never change colors.

Never change typography.

Never change spacing.

Never rename CSS classes.

Never remove animations.

Never remove transitions.

Keep UI exactly as designed unless explicitly instructed.

==========================================================

## DATABASE

Always follow DATABASE_SCHEMA.md exactly.

Never invent fields.

Never rename fields.

Never remove fields.

Never flatten the database structure.

Use Firebase Push ID.

Always preserve:

identity

payment

qr

studio

queue

status

createdAt

updatedAt

==========================================================

## FIREBASE

Never initialize Firebase twice.

Always use firebase-config.js.

Never hardcode Firebase configuration.

Never bypass service layer.

==========================================================

## IMPORT RULES

UI Layer

↓

booking.js

↓

Service Layer

↓

Firebase

Never call Firebase directly from UI.

==========================================================

## BUSINESS RULES

booking.html

CREATE only.

hasilpembayaran.html

READ only.

admin.html

READ + UPDATE only.

database.html

READ + SEARCH only.

==========================================================

## ERROR HANDLING

Always use try/catch.

Throw Error.

Never use alert().

Never use confirm().

Never silently ignore errors.

==========================================================

## COMMENT STYLE

Every file must contain professional comments.

Use section headers.

Explain responsibilities.

Keep comments concise.

==========================================================

## NAMING

Use camelCase.

Use descriptive names.

No abbreviations.

No single-letter variables except loop counters.

==========================================================

## BEFORE GENERATING CODE

Always ask yourself:

Am I changing architecture?

Am I breaking another module?

Am I duplicating logic?

Am I violating Single Responsibility?

Am I modifying stable code?

If the answer is YES,

STOP.

Generate a minimal revision instead.

==========================================================

## OUTPUT RULES

Prefer updating existing files.

Never create new files unless explicitly requested.

Never rename files.

Never move files.

Never delete files.

Always preserve backward compatibility.

==========================================================

## DEFAULT MODE

Minimal Invasive Refactor

Production Ready

Enterprise Standard

Maintain Existing Architecture

Never Over Engineer